From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] musb: gadget: rate-limited RX anomaly diagnostics (bulk-OUT
 stall investigation)

Temporary instrumentation for the sustained bulk-OUT stall (large adb
push / fastboot boot through usb-proxy). Silent unless the anomaly
actually occurs:

 * musb_g_rx(): log OVERRUN/INCOMPRX with RXCOUNT and the full RXCSR.
   Either flag on an OUT endpoint means the controller dropped or
   mangled a packet the host believes was ACKed. The stock code clears
   these flags silently.

 * rxstate(): log RXPKTRDY-with-RXCOUNT==0 givebacks. These are either
   genuine host ZLPs (adb sends one after every 4096-byte WRTE payload)
   or the requeue-flush race eating a data packet (see the 0001 patch);
   correlating them with a stalled stream distinguishes the two.

Applies on top of 0001-musb-gadget-service-pending-RX-packet-on-requeue.
Remove once the stall investigation concludes.

Signed-off-by: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
---
 drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c | 23 +++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 23 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c
@@ -584,6 +584,16 @@
 		fifo_count = musb_readw(epio, MUSB_RXCOUNT);
 
 		/*
+		 * Diagnostic (usb-proxy appliance): RXPKTRDY with RXCOUNT==0
+		 * is either a genuine host ZLP or the requeue-flush race
+		 * eating a data packet (see musb_ep_restart). Log it so a
+		 * stalled length-framed stream can be correlated.
+		 */
+		if (fifo_count == 0 && request->length > 0)
+			pr_info_ratelimited("musb rx-diag: %s RXPKTRDY with RXCOUNT==0 (host ZLP or flush race), csr %04x\n",
+					musb_ep->end_point.name, csr);
+
+		/*
 		 * Enable Mode 1 on RX transfers only when short_not_ok flag
 		 * is set. Currently short_not_ok flag is set only from
 		 * file_storage and f_mass_storage drivers
@@ -818,6 +828,18 @@
 	musb_dbg(musb, "<== %s, rxcsr %04x%s %p", musb_ep->end_point.name,
 			csr, dma ? " (dma)" : "", request);
 
+	/*
+	 * Diagnostic (usb-proxy appliance): OVERRUN or INCOMPRX on an OUT
+	 * endpoint means the controller dropped or mangled a packet the host
+	 * believes was ACKed. The stock code clears these flags silently.
+	 */
+	if (csr & (MUSB_RXCSR_P_OVERRUN | MUSB_RXCSR_INCOMPRX))
+		pr_info_ratelimited("musb rx-diag: %s csr %04x count %d%s%s\n",
+				musb_ep->end_point.name, csr,
+				musb_readw(epio, MUSB_RXCOUNT),
+				(csr & MUSB_RXCSR_P_OVERRUN) ? " OVERRUN" : "",
+				(csr & MUSB_RXCSR_INCOMPRX) ? " INCOMPRX" : "");
+
 	if (csr & MUSB_RXCSR_P_SENTSTALL) {
 		csr |= MUSB_RXCSR_P_WZC_BITS;
 		csr &= ~MUSB_RXCSR_P_SENTSTALL;
